<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-04-30"><hi rend="italic">April 30,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The American schooner <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi>, from Key West,
                            with part of the crew, was captured near San Cayetano, to the westward,
                            while, it is alleged, landing arms for the insurgents, and towed here
                            yesterday. The case subject to marine jurisdiction. I have seen admiral,
                            who tells me it is now under examination of the judge of instruction. I
                            have verbally asked for observance, as heretofore, of the protocol in
                            the trial of the Americans among them, and I shall confirm it in
                            writing.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>